structured.description: An `AuthenticationController` class that acts as a RESTful API for authentication purposes. The controller receives a `LoginRequest` object from the client and passes it to an `AuthenticationService` implementation for processing. Once the authentication is successful, the controller creates and returns a `ResponseEntity` object with the user ID and JWT token in the HTTP headers.

items.description: Is a Spring REST controller that implements the AuthenticationApi interface. It provides a login method that takes a valid LoginRequest object as input and returns a ResponseEntity with the user ID and JWT token in the HTTP headers. The class also includes a private method for creating the HTTP headers based on the returned AuthenticationData object.
items.name: AuthenticationController

items.description: Authenticates a user by calling the `loginService` and returning an `ResponseEntity` with the authentication data.

params.name: loginRequest
params.description: user's login details, containing the username and password for authentication by the `authenticationService`.

returns.description: a `ResponseEntity` object with an `OK` status and headers containing authentication data.

items.name: login

items.description: Creates HTTP headers with user ID and JWT token for login purposes based on input `AuthenticationData`.

params.name: authenticationData
params.description: user's login information, providing the user ID and JWT token for authentication purposes.

returns.description: a set of HTTP headers containing the user ID and JWT token for authentication purposes.

items.name: createLoginHeaders

structured.description: A controller class that implements the HousesApi interface to manage houses and their members. The HouseController handles HTTP requests for listing all houses, retrieving house details by id, adding and deleting house members, and listing all members of a specific house. It uses Spring Data JPA to interact with the database and Lombok for code generation.

items.description: Provides RESTful API endpoints for managing houses and their members. It handles requests to list all houses, get house details, list house members, add house members, and delete house members. The controller delegates tasks to the HouseService class for data retrieval and manipulation.
items.name: HouseController

items.description: Retrieves a list of houses, maps them to a REST API response format, and returns the result as a HTTP OK response. It uses pagination with a default page size of 200.

params.name: pageable
params.description:
pagination settings for retrieving houses, allowing to control the number of items returned per page and the current page number.

Destructured into Pageable parameters: page, size, and sort.

returns.description: a ResponseEntity containing a list of GetHouseDetailsResponseCommunityHouse objects.

usage.code:
Pageable pageable = PageRequest.of(0, 200);
ResponseEntity<GetHouseDetailsResponse> response = houseController.listAllHouses(pageable);

items.name: listAllHouses

items.description: Retrieves house details by ID, maps them to a REST API response object, and returns a ResponseEntity with a GetHouseDetailsResponse containing the mapped houses. If no matching record is found, it returns a ResponseEntity with a 404 status code.

params.name: houseId
params.description: identifier of the house whose details are to be retrieved and processed by the function.

returns.description: a ResponseEntity containing GetHouseDetailsResponse with houses.

items.name: getHouseDetails

items.description: Retrieves all members of a house with a specified ID, applies pagination using a pageable object, maps the result to a response API, and returns it as a ResponseEntity containing a ListHouseMembersResponse or a not-found error.

params.name: houseId
params.description: ID of the house for which all members are to be listed, as indicated by the log message and the subsequent method call to `houseService.getHouseMembersById`.

params.name: pageable
params.description:
page information for pagination, allowing for retrieval of a specific subset of members from the house with a specified size.

Pageable has default size set to 200 and no offset specified.

returns.description:
a ResponseEntity of ListHouseMembersResponse.

The ResponseEntity is of type ListHouseMembersResponse with members containing a set of HouseMemberSet converted from house member objects using houseMemberMapper.

items.name: listAllMembersOfHouse

items.description: Handles requests to add members to a house, converting provided data transfer objects (DTOs) into domain objects and storing them in the database. It returns a response indicating success or failure based on whether the operation was successful.

params.name: houseId
params.description: ID of the house to which members are being added, and it is used as a path variable.

params.name: request
params.description:
AddHouseMemberRequest object that contains a set of house member DTOs to be added to the specified house with id.

Destructured request: 
- `houseId`: String
- `members`: Set of HouseMember DTOs

returns.description:
a response entity containing an add house member response.

The response is of type `ResponseEntity` and contains an instance of `AddHouseMemberResponse`. This response includes a set of `HouseMember` objects, represented as `members`, in its attributes.

items.name: addHouseMembers

items.description: Handles a request to delete a member from a house with specified IDs. It logs the request and calls the `houseService.deleteMemberFromHouse` method to perform the deletion. If successful, it returns a response indicating no content; otherwise, it returns a not found status.

params.name: houseId
params.description: identifying code of a house to which a member is being deleted from.

params.name: memberId
params.description: unique identifier of the member to be deleted from the house with the specified `houseId`.

returns.description:
a `ResponseEntity` with either HTTP status NO CONTENT (204) or NOT FOUND (404).

The output is a ResponseEntity object with Void as its payload. It has a status code either HttpStatus.NO_CONTENT or HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND depending on whether the member was successfully deleted or not.

usage.description: This will attempt to remove the member with id "member123" from the house with id "12345".

items.name: deleteHouseMember
